recovered from the site of
the Battle of the Boyne, 1690.

02:56.943 --> 02:58.718
- Bloody hell.

02:58.745 --> 03:00.224
Can't we steal it?

03:01.648 --> 03:03.924
Well, we do have form.

03:06.953 --> 03:08.728
- So how are you doing?

03:08.755 --> 03:11.235
Do you feel the hand of history
on your shoulder?

03:11.257 --> 03:14.204
Around my throat, more like.

03:14.227 --> 03:15.570
- It's like looking
at the Promised Land

03:15.595 --> 03:17.597
through the wrong end
of a telescope.

03:17.630 --> 03:21.578
- Prime Minister,
I've been at this since 1972.

03:21.601 --> 03:23.547
I've retired three times.

03:23.570 --> 03:25.345
I have more comebacks
than Sinatra.

03:26.306 --> 03:30.311
Every time there is a chink
of light, they drag me back

03:30.343 --> 03:32.823
simply because I know them
better than anyone.

03:32.845 --> 03:38.295
But this time is
the first time I really felt...

03:39.819 --> 03:41.628
Yes, there's a chance.

03:41.654 --> 03:42.860
We can do this.

03:45.425 --> 03:47.268
- Do you say this
to all the prime ministers?

03:48.561 --> 03:49.904
- Of course.

03:50.763 --> 03:52.367
Only this time, I mean it.

03:53.466 --> 03:54.740
- Why now?

03:54.767 --> 03:56.576
- Well, because...

03:56.603 --> 03:59.675
young men fight
for the hell of it,

03:59.706 --> 04:03.552
but old men
care about their legacy.

04:03.576 --> 04:05.886
Now, I think
this is the right time.

04:06.980 --> 04:08.425
- Well, I hope you're right.

04:17.490 --> 04:20.494
Speaking of old men,
Ian disappearing like this

04:20.526 --> 04:21.732
isn't gonna help matters.

04:21.761 --> 04:23.263
- It'll keep him sweet.

04:24.430 --> 04:26.410
50 years of marriage.

04:27.467 --> 04:30.414
It's rumored it's the last time
he said yes to anything.

