05:39.405 --> 05:41.646
<i>that that republic</i>

05:41.674 --> 05:46.384
<i>must have some say
in our province.</i>

05:46.412 --> 05:49.086
<i>We say never!</i>

05:49.115 --> 05:52.119
<i>Never! Never!</i>

05:52.352 --> 05:53.797
Never.

05:58.591 --> 06:01.868
Bernie, Bernie, you need
to go easy on the garlic.

06:01.894 --> 06:04.033
- <i>Even though the pressure is on
to make</i> a <i>deal...</i>

06:04.063 --> 06:06.509
- I'm telling-I'm serious.

06:07.967 --> 06:10.072
The last-
the last time I cooked,

06:10.103 --> 06:12.049
the girls said
I nearly poisoned them.

06:13.506 --> 06:15.383
- <i>In the north,
over civil' rights.</i>

06:15.408 --> 06:16.978
<i>In brief,
because the Catholics wanted...</i>

06:17.009 --> 06:18.113
- Ah.

06:18.144 --> 06:20.522
Well, don't blame me.
Blame Delia.

06:20.546 --> 06:22.116
- <i>And the Protestants
Wanted to remain</i>

06:22.148 --> 06:24.059
<i>part of the United Kingdom,</i>

06:24.083 --> 06:25.426
<i>and they've been at it
ever since.</i>

06:25.451 --> 06:26.452
- Right.

06:26.486 --> 06:27.760
- <i>The main players
on the Republican side...</i>

06:27.787 --> 06:30.461
- All right, all right.
Meatballs it is, then. Mm-hmm.

06:30.490 --> 06:33.437
Well, it's not luck we need.

06:33.459 --> 06:35.530
It's divine intervention. Hmm.

06:35.561 --> 06:36.562
Bye.

06:36.596 --> 06:38.576
- <i>The long history
of acrimony and distrust</i>

06:38.598 --> 06:40.077
<i>that comes
with Northern Ireland.</i>

06:40.099 --> 06:43.808
<i>Such an outcome is very much
par for the course.</i>

06:43.836 --> 06:46.476
- <i>But if We're talking about
public perception,</i>

06:46.506 --> 06:48.452
<i>we can go back even further:</i>

06:48.474 --> 06:51.011
<i>the Remembrance Day
bombing in 1987</i>

06:51.043 --> 06:53.080
<i>and that moving
and memorable interview</i>

